#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc35:pts-cs0.3"
msgid "Pācittiyakaṇḍa"
msgstr "The chapter on confession (<i lang=\"pli\">pācittiya</i>)"

#. </p><p> 
#. VAR: Bhojanavagga → paṭha­ma­pavāra­ṇa­sikkhā­padaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc35:pts-cs0.4"
msgid "Bhojanavagga"
msgstr "Monks’ Confession 35"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc35:pts-cs0.5"
msgid "35. Pavāraṇāsikkhāpada"
msgstr "The training rule on satisfaction"

#. </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc35:pts-cs0.6"
msgid ""
msgstr "Origin story"

#. </h2><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc35:pts-cs1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "First sub-story"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="1"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.35.1"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.326"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa765"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc35:pts-cs1.1"
msgid "Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme."
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc35:pts-cs1.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena aññataro brāhmaṇo bhikkhū nimantetvā bhojesi."
msgstr "At that time a certain brahmin had invited the monks for a meal."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc35:pts-cs1.3"
msgid "Bhikkhū bhuttāvī pavāritā ñātikulāni gantvā ekacce bhuñjiṃsu ekacce piṇḍapātaṃ ādāya agamaṃsu."
msgstr "After the monks had eaten and expressed their satisfaction, they went to their respective families, where some ate and some took away almsfood."

#. </p><p>
#. VAR: paṭivissake → paṭivisake (yojanā)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc35:pts-cs1.4"
msgid "Atha kho so brāhmaṇo paṭivissake etadavoca—"
msgstr "Soon afterwards that brahmin said to his neighbors,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc35:pts-cs1.5"
msgid "“bhikkhū mayā, ayyā, santappitā."
msgstr "“The monks have been satisfied by me."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc35:pts-cs1.6"
msgid "Etha, tumhepi santappessāmī”ti."
msgstr "Come, and I’ll satisfy you, too.”"

#. VAR: ayyo → ayya (s1-3)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc35:pts-cs1.7"
msgid "Te evamāhaṃsu—“kiṃ tvaṃ, ayyo, amhe santappessasi?"
msgstr "“How could you satisfy us?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc35:pts-cs1.8"
msgid "Yepi tayā nimantitā tepi amhākaṃ gharāni āgantvā ekacce bhuñjiṃsu ekacce piṇḍapātaṃ ādāya agamaṃsū”ti."
msgstr "Those monks who were invited by you came to our houses. Some of them ate there and some took away almsfood.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="2"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa766"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc35:pts-cs1.9"
msgid "Atha kho so brāhmaṇo ujjhāyati khiyyati vipāceti—"
msgstr "That brahmin complained and criticized those monks,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc35:pts-cs1.10"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma bhadantā amhākaṃ ghare bhuñjitvā aññatra bhuñjissanti."
msgstr "“How can the Venerables eat in our house and afterwards eat elsewhere?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc35:pts-cs1.11"
msgid "Na cāhaṃ paṭibalo yāvadatthaṃ dātun”ti."
msgstr "Am I not able to give them as much as they need?”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="3"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.82"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa767"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc35:pts-cs1.12"
msgid "Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū tassa brāhmaṇassa ujjhāyantassa khiyyantassa vipācentassa."
msgstr "The monks heard the complaints of that brahmin,"

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.327"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc35:pts-cs1.13"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā … pe …"
msgstr "and the monks of few desires …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc35:pts-cs1.14"
msgid "te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "complained and criticized those monks,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc35:pts-cs1.15"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma bhikkhū bhuttāvī pavāritā aññatra bhuñjissantī”ti … pe …"
msgstr "“How can those monks finish their meal and express their satisfaction, and then eat elsewhere?” …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc35:pts-cs1.16"
msgid "“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, bhikkhū bhuttāvī pavāritā aññatra bhuñjantī”ti?"
msgstr "“Is it true, monks, that monks did this?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc35:pts-cs1.17"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc35:pts-cs1.18"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "The Buddha criticized them, “…"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc35:pts-cs1.19"
msgid "kathañhi nāma te, bhikkhave, moghapurisā bhuttāvī pavāritā aññatra bhuñjissanti."
msgstr "How can those foolish men finish their meal and express their satisfaction, and then eat elsewhere?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc35:pts-cs1.20"
msgid "Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc35:pts-cs1.21"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc35:pts-cs1.21a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Preliminary ruling"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="4"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa768"></a>
#. <span class="rule"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc35:pts-cs1.22"
msgid "“Yo pana bhikkhu bhuttāvī pavārito khādanīyaṃ vā bhojanīyaṃ vā khādeyya vā bhuñjeyya vā, pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr "‘If a monk who has eaten and expressed his satisfaction eats staple or non-staple food, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”"

#. </span>
#. </p><p class="endsection"><a class="sc" id="5"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa769"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc35:pts-cs1.23"
msgid "Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti."
msgstr "In this way the Master laid down this training rule for the monks."

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc35:pts-cs2.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Second sub-story"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="6"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.35.2"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa770"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc35:pts-cs2.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū gilānānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ paṇīte piṇḍapāte nīharanti."
msgstr "Soon afterwards the monks were bringing back fine almsfood for the sick monks."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc35:pts-cs2.2"
msgid "Gilānā na cittarūpaṃ bhuñjanti."
msgstr "But because they were not able to eat as much as they had intended,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc35:pts-cs2.3"
msgid "Tāni bhikkhū chaṭṭenti."
msgstr "the monks threw the leftovers away."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc35:pts-cs2.4"
msgid "Assosi kho bhagavā uccāsaddaṃ mahāsaddaṃ kākoravasaddaṃ."
msgstr "The Master heard the loud sound of crows cawing,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc35:pts-cs2.5"
msgid "Sutvāna āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ āmantesi—"
msgstr "and he asked Venerable Ānanda,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc35:pts-cs2.6"
msgid "“kiṃ nu kho so, ānanda, uccāsaddo mahāsaddo kākoravasaddo”ti?"
msgstr "“Ānanda, why is there this loud sound of crows cawing?”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc35:pts-cs2.7"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā ānando bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesi."
msgstr "Ānanda told him about what had happened, and the Master said:"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc35:pts-cs2.8"
msgid "“Bhuñjeyyuṃ panānanda, bhikkhū gilānātirittan”ti."
msgstr "“But Ānanda, don’t the monks eat the leftovers from those who are sick?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc35:pts-cs2.9"
msgid "“Na bhuñjeyyuṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“No, Master, they don’t.”"

#. </p><p><a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.328"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc35:pts-cs2.10"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—"
msgstr "Soon afterwards the Master gave a teaching and addressed the monks,"

#. <span class="rule"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc35:pts-cs2.11"
msgid "“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, gilānassa ca agilānassa ca atirittaṃ bhuñjituṃ."
msgstr "“Monks, I allow you to eat the leftovers from those who are sick, and also from those who are not sick."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc35:pts-cs2.12"
msgid "Evañca pana, bhikkhave, atirittaṃ kātabbaṃ—"
msgstr "And, monks, this is how you make food leftover:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc35:pts-cs2.13"
msgid "‘alametaṃ sabban’ti."
msgstr "‘I’ve had enough of all of this.’"

#. </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc35:pts-cs2.14"
msgid "Evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And so, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc35:pts-cs2.14a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="7"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa771"></a> 
#. <span class="rule">
#. <i lang="pli">Pavārito</i>, often translated as “invited,” but the word also means “satisfied.” In the present case, the contextual meaning (see below) is that the monk has expressed his satisfaction after being invited to take more.
#. VAR: khādanīyaṃ → khādaniyaṃ (pts1)
#. VAR: bhojanīyaṃ → bhojaniyaṃ (pts1)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc35:pts-cs2.15"
msgid "“Yo pana bhikkhu bhuttāvī pavārito anatirittaṃ khādanīyaṃ vā bhojanīyaṃ vā khādeyya vā bhuñjeyya vā, pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr "‘If a monk who has eaten and expressed his satisfaction eats staple or non-staple food that is not left over, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”"

#. </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc35:pts-cs2.16"
msgid "(<em>35</em>:<strong>84</strong>)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc35:pts-cs3.1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="8"></a><a class="pts-cs-empty" id="bu-pc.35.3"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.35.3.1"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa772"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc35:pts-cs3.1.1"
msgid "Yo panāti"
msgstr "A:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc35:pts-cs3.1.2"
msgid "yo yādiso … pe …"
msgstr "whoever …"

#. </span>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc35:pts-cs3.1.3"
msgid "bhikkhūti"
msgstr "Monk:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc35:pts-cs3.1.4"
msgid "… pe …"
msgstr "… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a complete Order through a procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is unchallengeable and fit to stand—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc35:pts-cs3.1.5"
msgid "ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti."
msgstr "this sort of monk is meant in this case."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="9"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa773"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc35:pts-cs3.1.6"
msgid "Bhuttāvī nāma"
msgstr "Who has eaten:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc35:pts-cs3.1.7"
msgid "pañcannaṃ bhojanānaṃ aññataraṃ bhojanaṃ antamaso kusaggenapi bhuttaṃ hoti."
msgstr "who has eaten any of the five staple foods, even just what fits on the tip of a blade of grass."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="10"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa774"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc35:pts-cs3.1.8"
msgid "Pavārito nāma"
msgstr "Expressed his satisfaction:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"><a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.329"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc35:pts-cs3.1.9"
msgid "asanaṃ paññāyati, bhojanaṃ paññāyati, hatthapāse ṭhito abhiharati, paṭikkhepo paññāyati."
msgstr "there is eating; there is staple food; it is offered by one standing within arm’s reach; there is a refusal."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="11"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa775"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc35:pts-cs3.1.10"
msgid "Anatirittaṃ nāma"
msgstr "Not left over:"

#. </span><span class="gloss">
#. <i lang="pli">Akappiyakataṃ hoti</i>, literally, “It is done with what is not allowable.”The “it,” both here and below, refers to the ceremony of making it allowable, and the “what” refers to the food.
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc35:pts-cs3.1.11"
msgid "akappiyakataṃ hoti,"
msgstr "the making it leftover is done with food that is not allowable;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc35:pts-cs3.1.12"
msgid "appaṭiggahitakataṃ hoti,"
msgstr "it is done with food that has not been received;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc35:pts-cs3.1.13"
msgid "anuccāritakataṃ hoti,"
msgstr "it is done with food that is not held in hand;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc35:pts-cs3.1.14"
msgid "ahatthapāse kataṃ hoti,"
msgstr "it is done by one who is not within arm’s reach;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc35:pts-cs3.1.15"
msgid "abhuttāvinā kataṃ hoti,"
msgstr "it is done by one who has not finished eating;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc35:pts-cs3.1.16"
msgid "bhuttāvinā pavāritena āsanā vuṭṭhitena kataṃ hoti,"
msgstr "it is done by one who has finished eating, who has expressed his satisfaction, but who has risen from his seat;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc35:pts-cs3.1.17"
msgid "“alametaṃ sabban”ti avuttaṃ hoti,"
msgstr "“I’ve had enough of all of this,” has not been said;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc35:pts-cs3.1.18"
msgid "na gilānātirittaṃ hoti—"
msgstr "it is not leftover from one who is sick—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc35:pts-cs3.1.19"
msgid "etaṃ anatirittaṃ nāma."
msgstr "this is called “not leftover.”"

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="12"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa776"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc35:pts-cs3.1.20"
msgid "Atirittaṃ nāma"
msgstr "Left over:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc35:pts-cs3.1.21"
msgid "kappiyakataṃ hoti,"
msgstr "the making it leftover is done with food that is allowable;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc35:pts-cs3.1.22"
msgid "paṭiggahitakataṃ hoti,"
msgstr "it is done with food that has been received;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc35:pts-cs3.1.23"
msgid "uccāritakataṃ hoti,"
msgstr "it is done with food that is held in hand;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc35:pts-cs3.1.24"
msgid "hatthapāse kataṃ hoti,"
msgstr "it is done by one who is within arm’s reach;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc35:pts-cs3.1.25"
msgid "bhuttāvinā kataṃ hoti,"
msgstr "it is done by one who has finished eating;"

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.330"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc35:pts-cs3.1.26"
msgid "bhuttāvinā pavāritena āsanā avuṭṭhitena kataṃ hoti,"
msgstr "it is done by one who has finished eating, who has expressed his satisfaction, and who has not risen from his seat;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc35:pts-cs3.1.27"
msgid "“alametaṃ sabban”ti vuttaṃ hoti,"
msgstr "“I’ve had enough of all of this,” has been said;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc35:pts-cs3.1.28"
msgid "gilānātirittaṃ hoti—"
msgstr "it is leftover from one who is sick—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc35:pts-cs3.1.29"
msgid "etaṃ atirittaṃ nāma."
msgstr "this is called “leftover.”"

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="13"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.83"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa777"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc35:pts-cs3.1.30"
msgid "Khādanīyaṃ nāma"
msgstr "Non-staple food:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc35:pts-cs3.1.31"
msgid "pañca bhojanāni—yāmakālikaṃ sattāhakālikaṃ yāvajīvikaṃ ṭhapetvā avasesaṃ khādanīyaṃ nāma."
msgstr "apart from the five staple foods, the post-midday tonics, the seven-day tonics, and the lifetime tonics—the rest is called “non-staple food.”"

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="14"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa778"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc35:pts-cs3.1.32"
msgid "Bhojanīyaṃ nāma"
msgstr "Staple food:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc35:pts-cs3.1.33"
msgid "pañca bhojanāni—"
msgstr "there are five kinds of staple food:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc35:pts-cs3.1.34"
msgid "odano, kummāso, sattu, maccho, maṃsaṃ."
msgstr "cooked grain, porridge, flour, fish, and meat."

#. </span>
#. </p><hr><p><a class="sc" id="15"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa779"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc35:pts-cs3.1.35"
msgid "“Khādissāmi bhuñjissāmī”ti paṭiggaṇhāti, āpatti dukkaṭassa ajjhohāre ajjhohāre āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "If he receives it intending to eat it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct. For every mouthful, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc35:pts-cs3.2.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Permutations"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="16"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.35.3.2"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.331"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa780"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc35:pts-cs3.2.1"
msgid "Anatiritte anatirittasaññī khādanīyaṃ vā bhojanīyaṃ vā khādati vā bhuñjati vā, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "If it is not leftover, and he does not perceive it as leftover, and he eats staple or non-staple food, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc35:pts-cs3.2.2"
msgid "Anatiritte vematiko khādanīyaṃ vā bhojanīyaṃ vā khādati vā bhuñjati vā, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "If it is not leftover, but he is unsure of it, and he eats staple or non-staple food, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc35:pts-cs3.2.3"
msgid "Anatiritte atirittasaññī khādanīyaṃ vā bhojanīyaṃ vā khādati vā bhuñjati vā, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "If it is not leftover, but he perceives it as leftover, and he eats staple or non-staple food, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="17"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa781"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc35:pts-cs3.2.4"
msgid "Yāmakālikaṃ sattāhakālikaṃ yāvajīvikaṃ āhāratthāya paṭiggaṇhāti, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If he receives post-midday tonics, seven-day tonics, or lifetime tonics for the purpose of food, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc35:pts-cs3.2.5"
msgid "Ajjhohāre ajjhohāre āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "For every mouthful, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc35:pts-cs3.2.6"
msgid "Atiritte anatirittasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If it is leftover, but he does not perceive it as leftover, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc35:pts-cs3.2.7"
msgid "Atiritte vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If it is leftover, but he is unsure if it is, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc35:pts-cs3.2.8"
msgid "Atiritte atirittasaññī, anāpatti."
msgstr "If it is leftover, and he perceives it as leftover, there is no offense."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc35:pts-cs3.3.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Non-offenses"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="18"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.35.3.3"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa782"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc35:pts-cs3.3.1"
msgid "Anāpatti—"
msgstr "There is no offense:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc35:pts-cs3.3.2"
msgid "atirittaṃ kārāpetvā bhuñjati,"
msgstr "if he eats it after getting it made leftover;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc35:pts-cs3.3.3"
msgid "“atirittaṃ kārāpetvā bhuñjissāmī”ti paṭiggaṇhāti,"
msgstr "if he receives it with the intention of getting it made leftover and then eating it;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc35:pts-cs3.3.4"
msgid "aññassatthāya haranto gacchati,"
msgstr "if he is taking food for the benefit of someone else;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc35:pts-cs3.3.5"
msgid "gilānassa sesakaṃ bhuñjati,"
msgstr "if he eats the leftovers from a sick person;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc35:pts-cs3.3.6"
msgid "yāmakālikaṃ sattāhakālikaṃ yāvajīvikaṃ sati paccaye paribhuñjati,"
msgstr "if, when there is a reason, he makes use of post-midday tonics, seven-day tonics, or lifetime tonics;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc35:pts-cs3.3.7"
msgid "ummattakassa,"
msgstr "if he is insane;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc35:pts-cs3.3.8"
msgid "ādikammikassāti."
msgstr "if he is the first offender."

#. </p><hr><p class="endsutta"><a class="sc" id="19"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa783"></a>
#. VAR: Pavāraṇāsikkhāpadaṃ → paṭha­ma­pavāra­ṇa­sikkhā­padaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc35:pts-cs3.3.9"
msgid "Pavāraṇāsikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ pañcamaṃ."
msgstr "The fifth rule, the training rule on satisfaction, is finished."

